<h1>The M誰mis Network</h1>

<p>It currently takes some technological savvy to comprehend the state of the M誰mis network. If you have some of that, you might like to check out:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="http://repo.dhappy.org/.../git/">Git Repository</a></li>
  <li><a href="crx">Chrome Extension</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://groups.google.com/group/tip-dev">Developers Listserv</a></li>
</ul>

<section>
<h1>1.0</h1>

<ol>
<li>User</li>
<li><a href="http://www.google.com/chrome/">Chrome</a></li>
<li><a href="crx">Chrome extension</a></li>
<li><a href="java/src/">Java</a> <a href="java/src/org/dhappy/mimis/CacheAgentApplet.java">applet</a></li>
<li><a href="http://neo4j.org">Neo4j</a></li>
<li>Cache Agents:
<ul>
<li><a href="java/src/org/dhappy/mimis/SmackGMailConnection.java"><acronym title="Extensible Message Passing Protocol">XMPP</acronym></a></li>
<li><a href="java/src/org/dhappy/mimis/FileLoader.java">File System</a></li>
<li><a href="http://mina.apache.org/">P2P</a></li>
<li>HTTP direct to User</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>

<p>The Neo4j instance is used by the agents to manage their behaviors. It is also caching information from other M誰mis instances running on the network.</p>

<p>Much of the information in Neo4j is a persistent shared metadata cache.</p>
